  • Method Details

    • getNumSamples

      public int getNumSamples()
      The exact number of audio samples analyzed from this track. See also analysis_sample_rate.

    • getDuration

      public double getDuration()
      Length of the track in seconds.

    • getSampleMd5

      public String getSampleMd5()
      This field will always contain the empty string

    • getOffsetSeconds

      public int getOffsetSeconds()
      An offset to the start of the region of the track that was analyzed. (As the entire track is analyzed, this should always be 0.)

    • getWindowSeconds

      public int getWindowSeconds()
      The length of the region of the track was analyzed, if a subset of the track was analyzed. (As the entire track is analyzed, this should always be 0.)

    • getAnalysisSampleRate

      public int getAnalysisSampleRate()
      The sample rate used to decode and analyze this track. May differ from the actual sample rate of this track available on Spotify.

    • getAnalysisChannels

      public int getAnalysisChannels()
      The number of channels used for analysis. If 1, all channels are summed together to mono before analysis.

    • getEndOfFadeIn

      public double getEndOfFadeIn()
      The time, in seconds, at which the track's fade-in period ends. If the track has no fade-in, this will be 0.0.

    • getStartOfFadeOut

      public double getStartOfFadeOut()
      The time, in seconds, at which the track's fade-out period starts. If the track has no fade-out, this should match the track's length.

    • getLoudness

      public double getLoudness()
      The overall loudness of a track in decibels (dB). Loudness values are averaged across the entire track and are useful for comparing relative loudness of tracks. Loudness is the quality of a sound that is the primary psychological correlate of physical strength (amplitude). Values typically range between -60 and 0 db.

    • getTempo

      public double getTempo()
      The overall estimated tempo of a track in beats per minute (BPM). In musical terminology, tempo is the speed or pace of a given piece and derives directly from the average beat duration.

    • getTempoConfidence

      public double getTempoConfidence()
      The confidence, from 0.0 to 1.0, of the reliability of the tempo.

    • getTimeSignature

      public int getTimeSignature()
      An estimated time signature. The time signature (meter) is a notational convention to specify how many beats are in each bar (or measure). The time signature ranges from 3 to 7 indicating time signatures of "3/4", to "7/4".

    • getTimeSignatureConfidence

      public double getTimeSignatureConfidence()
      The confidence, from 0.0 to 1.0, of the reliability of the time_signature.

    • getKey

      public int getKey()
      The key the track is in. Integers map to pitches using standard Pitch Class notation. E.g. 0 = C, 1 = C♯/D♭, 2 = D, and so on. If no key was detected, the value is -1.

    • getKeyConfidence

      public double getKeyConfidence()
      The confidence, from 0.0 to 1.0, of the reliability of the key.

    • getMode

      public int getMode()
      Mode indicates the modality (major or minor) of a track, the type of scale from which its melodic content is derived. Major is represented by 1 and minor is 0.

    • getModeConfidence

      public double getModeConfidence()
      The confidence, from 0.0 to 1.0, of the reliability of the mode.

    • getCode

      public String getCode()
      An Echo Nest Musical Fingerprint (ENMFP) codestring for this track.

    • getCodeVersion

      public double getCodeVersion()
      A version number for the Echo Nest Musical Fingerprint format used in the codestring field.

    • getEchoprint

      public String getEchoprint()
      An EchoPrint codestring for this track.

    • getEchoPrintVersion

      public double getEchoPrintVersion()
      A version number for the EchoPrint format used in the echoprintstring field.

    • getSynch

      public String getSynch()
      A Synchstring for this track.

    • getSynchVersion

      public double getSynchVersion()
      A version number for the Synchstring used in the synchstring field.

    • getRhythm

      public String getRhythm()
      A Rhythmstring for this track. The format of this string is similar to the Synchstring.

    • getRhythmVersion

      public double getRhythmVersion()
      A version number for the Rhythmstring used in the rhythmstring field.
